Hello, Step by step documentation to connect Bitbucket using visual studio 2015 community

Step -1
	Create new repository on Bitbucket any name you want i.e "PinstormRepository" - check
	
	Click on url copy repository link i.e "git clone https://vijaybabar@bitbucket.org/kalptechsystems/pinstormrepository.git" - check
	

Step -2
	Open visual studio 2015 community -> Click view -> Team Explorer - check
	
	Click Home - check
	
	Click manage connections -> Local git repositories -> Click clone -> Enter the repository to clone into first textbox i.e= "https://bitbucket.org/kalptechsystems/pinstormrepository" second textbox add local working dir "folder path that you want to create mvc project ="D:\MVC5_Projects\PinstormPortal" " -> Click clone btn - check						

	Now repository created -> Click on that repository -> Create solutions -> new-> New Project or may be Open Existsing project -> Create MVC Project -> Viual C# -> MVC5	-> Create - Check
	
	---Optional start---
	go to settings -> Global Settings -> username = "vijay babar"
										Email address = "vijbab.kalp@gmail.com"
										Defalt repository location = "D\MVC5_Projects\PinstormPortal" -> Click update

										
	go to settings -> Repository Settings -> Remotes -> Add -> 
										Name = "PinstormRepository"	
										bitbucket repository url like this = "https://bitbucket.org/kalptechsystems/pinstormrepository" -> Save it
	---Optional End---	
									
Step -3
	go to changes -> type with comment-> select commit and Push -> Commit

	Now Check Bitbucket Repository -> hopefully added project on to it - enjoy
	
	Go to home controller -> Edit it (Notice File get auto checkout) -> Right click it and Commit it with necessary comment 	
	
	Thank you
